5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING HUMAN RIGHTS LAWS; PROHIBITING
6 ALLOWING A STATE OR LOCAL GOVERNMENT AGENCY FROM REQUIRING OR REQUESTING TO
7 HAVE A DIVERSITY STATEMENT OR GRANTING ANY PREFERENTIAL TREATMENT BASED ON THE
8 SUBMISSION OF A DIVERSITY STATEMENT; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION; AND PROVIDING
9 DEFINITIONS.”
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Diversity statements prohibited allowed -- exception. (1) A state or
14 local government agency may not require, request, solicit, or compel a person to provide develop and publish a
15 diversity statement.
16 (2) A state or local government agency may not grant any form of preferential consideration or
17 treatment to a person who, with or without solicitation from the state or local government agency, provides a
18 diversity statement.
19 (3)(2) If federal law requires a state or local government agency to accept or require adopt a diversity
20 statement, then the state or local government agency:
21 (a) may accept the diversity statement only to the extent required under federal law; and
22 (b) shall limit consideration of the information contained in the diversity statement to the extent
23 necessary to satisfy the requirement under federal law.
24 (4)(3) Nothing in this section limits or prohibits a state or local government agency from establishing
25 policies that are necessary to comply with state or federal law, including laws relating to prohibited
26 discrimination and harassment.
