1 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 2], unless the context clearly
2 indicates otherwise, the following definitions apply:
3 (1) "Diversity statement" means a submission, statement, or document that promotes or is
4 intended to promote differential treatment based on an individual's race, color, ethnicity, sex, sexual orientation,
5 national origin, religion, or gender identity formal expression, statement, or document detailing a commitment to
6 embracing diversity, equity, and inclusion.
7 (2) "State or local government agency" means:
8 (a) any branch, department, office, board, bureau, commission, agency, university unit, college, or
9 other instrumentality of state government; or
10 (b) a county, city, town, school district, or other unit of local government and any instrumentality of
11 local government.
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 2] are intended to be
14 codified as a new chapter in Title 49, and the provisions of Title 49 apply to [sections 1 through 2].
